Co-opting in El Mundo

Co-ops are making their way into neighborhoods and homes around the world. They are not just produced and distributed in El Mundo. Work spaces for co-ops are being refurbished by the city of Oakland for co-ops in startup mode in the U.S. There is a co-op building in Sweden that houses a series of co-ops that prepare communal meals at their homes, have meetings in the building, and shop for groceries in a connected supermarket. “The infrastructure of co-operative co-operatives can be seen in Sweden, where the city of Lund has is an apartment-dwelling co-operative co-operative that is also a member of a regional co-operative housing organisation that also runs a co-operative grocery store”, stated Safouane.

Once built in El Mundo, the El Mundo working co-op building will have a solar-paneled roof, a storefront in the Kitchener neighborhood, and next year plants for 2000 trees will be developed. The working co-op building is a great model for others to follow, as stated by the three participants in the presentation.
